[
    {
        "text": "[MUSIC PLAYING]",
        "start": 0.0,
        "duration": 2.82
    },
    {
        "text": " Hi.",
        "start": 2.82,
        "duration": 0.55
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm Dianna.",
        "start": 3.37,
        "duration": 0.55
    },
    {
        "text": "You're watching \"Physics\nGirl,\" and I'm here",
        "start": 3.92,
        "duration": 1.93
    },
    {
        "text": "with Zach Weinersmith, who\nis the author and mastermind",
        "start": 5.85,
        "duration": 4.26
    },
    {
        "text": "behind SMBC Comics.",
        "start": 10.11,
        "duration": 1.844
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: Yes.",
        "start": 11.954,
        "duration": 0.916
    },
    {
        "text": " Saturday Morning\nBreakfast Cereal.",
        "start": 12.87,
        "duration": 1.65
    },
    {
        "text": "I've seen your comics like\nall over the internet,",
        "start": 14.52,
        "duration": 2.37
    },
    {
        "text": "before I knew that\nthey were yours.",
        "start": 16.89,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": "And I'm sure this\nis pretty common.",
        "start": 18.47,
        "duration": 1.1
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah.",
        "start": 19.57,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "You Have this one comic\nthat's about a math teacher.",
        "start": 20.07,
        "duration": 2.605
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH:\nI was surprised",
        "start": 22.675,
        "duration": 1.375
    },
    {
        "text": "about how well that did it,\nbecause it was kind of mean.",
        "start": 24.05,
        "duration": 1.79
    },
    {
        "text": "Well, it was\nfunny-- that was one",
        "start": 25.84,
        "duration": 0.815
    },
    {
        "text": "where I got a whole\nlot of math teachers,",
        "start": 26.655,
        "duration": 1.48
    },
    {
        "text": "and I was surprised, like math\nteachers who were still working",
        "start": 28.135,
        "duration": 2.105
    },
    {
        "text": "were like, this is exactly it.",
        "start": 30.24,
        "duration": 1.302
    },
    {
        "text": "And I was like, mm.",
        "start": 31.542,
        "duration": 0.791
    },
    {
        "text": " Oh, Zach.",
        "start": 32.333,
        "duration": 1.907
    },
    {
        "text": " I know, right?",
        "start": 34.24,
        "duration": 0.77
    },
    {
        "text": " Oh, that's so--",
        "start": 35.01,
        "duration": 0.79
    },
    {
        "text": "oh, poor children.",
        "start": 35.8,
        "duration": 1.229
    },
    {
        "text": " Thank you so much for--",
        "start": 37.029,
        "duration": 1.041
    },
    {
        "text": "the real reason\nthat you're here is",
        "start": 38.07,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "to answer some physics riddles.",
        "start": 39.99,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": " Yes.",
        "start": 41.31,
        "duration": 0.62
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, good.",
        "start": 41.93,
        "duration": 0.64
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah.",
        "start": 42.57,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, I'm going to start\nwith a warm-up, which",
        "start": 43.069,
        "duration": 1.901
    },
    {
        "text": "is more of like a\nphysics trivia question.",
        "start": 44.97,
        "duration": 2.051
    },
    {
        "text": " OK.",
        "start": 47.021,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": " And I didn't get it right.",
        "start": 47.52,
        "duration": 1.166
    },
    {
        "text": "So, good luck.",
        "start": 48.686,
        "duration": 0.994
    },
    {
        "text": "What are the base SI units?",
        "start": 49.68,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: Oh,\nlike the most fundamental?",
        "start": 52.16,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: Yes.",
        "start": 54.16,
        "duration": 0.791
    },
    {
        "text": "Pause here if you want to\nthink about the answer first.",
        "start": 54.951,
        "duration": 2.739
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: Grams.",
        "start": 57.69,
        "duration": 1.02
    },
    {
        "text": " I'm going to give\nyou the point for gram,",
        "start": 58.71,
        "duration": 1.791
    },
    {
        "text": "but it's actually kilograms.",
        "start": 60.501,
        "duration": 1.419
    },
    {
        "text": "A kilogram is weirdly defined\noff of a physical object--",
        "start": 61.92,
        "duration": 3.5
    },
    {
        "text": "a cylinder kept in\nFrance called the Big K.",
        "start": 65.42,
        "duration": 2.275
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH:\nMeters, obviously.",
        "start": 67.695,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "[DING]",
        "start": 69.195,
        "duration": 0.495
    },
    {
        "text": " This is such an evil\nquestion for someone",
        "start": 69.69,
        "duration": 1.65
    },
    {
        "text": "who hasn't studied\nphysics for a long time.",
        "start": 71.34,
        "duration": 1.59
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah, I'm just\ntrying to think what--",
        "start": 72.93,
        "duration": 1.27
    },
    {
        "text": "I mean, because\nthere are obviously",
        "start": 74.2,
        "duration": 0.95
    },
    {
        "text": "all the bigger aggregate units.",
        "start": 75.15,
        "duration": 1.62
    },
    {
        "text": "Like does joules\ncount as fundamental?",
        "start": 76.77,
        "duration": 1.95
    },
    {
        "text": " No.",
        "start": 78.72,
        "duration": 0.69
    },
    {
        "text": "Well, then there would\nbe seconds, of course.",
        "start": 79.41,
        "duration": 1.16
    },
    {
        "text": "[DING]",
        "start": 80.57,
        "duration": 0.55
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: Yes.",
        "start": 81.12,
        "duration": 0.791
    },
    {
        "text": "The second is defined off\nof the frequency of light",
        "start": 81.911,
        "duration": 2.179
    },
    {
        "text": "from energy-level transitions\nin a cesium 133 atom-- so weird.",
        "start": 84.09,
        "duration": 3.919
    },
    {
        "text": " And there's more.",
        "start": 88.009,
        "duration": 0.791
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, well, there must be\na charge unit, right?",
        "start": 88.8,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": " So that's also\none that I guessed.",
        "start": 91.08,
        "duration": 1.88
    },
    {
        "text": "I thought the coulomb\nwas a base SI unit.",
        "start": 92.96,
        "duration": 1.77
    },
    {
        "text": " Right.",
        "start": 94.73,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Why not?",
        "start": 95.23,
        "duration": 0.95
    },
    {
        "text": " I don't know why not.",
        "start": 96.18,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "It's probably a\nhistorical reason.",
        "start": 97.86,
        "duration": 1.56
    },
    {
        "text": "I just want you to\nknow that you've",
        "start": 99.42,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "got all the ones that I got.",
        "start": 100.92,
        "duration": 1.47
    },
    {
        "text": "And the rest of them are weird.",
        "start": 102.39,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": " What else do you\nneed to describe what's",
        "start": 104.63,
        "duration": 1.75
    },
    {
        "text": "going on in the universe?",
        "start": 106.38,
        "duration": 1.347
    },
    {
        "text": " [LAUGHING] We've got a\npracticing physicist over here,",
        "start": 107.727,
        "duration": 2.333
    },
    {
        "text": "like dying to answer do\nyou know what they are?",
        "start": 110.06,
        "duration": 1.959
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah, what is it?",
        "start": 112.019,
        "duration": 0.79
    },
    {
        "text": "LLOYD: I think\nthere's one for light.",
        "start": 112.809,
        "duration": 1.581
    },
    {
        "text": "It's either lumens or candela.",
        "start": 114.39,
        "duration": 2.33
    },
    {
        "text": "[DING]",
        "start": 116.72,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: Yeah!",
        "start": 117.22,
        "duration": 0.67
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah!",
        "start": 117.89,
        "duration": 0.43
    },
    {
        "text": "That's some of the weird ones.",
        "start": 118.32,
        "duration": 0.99
    },
    {
        "text": "I never would have guessed.",
        "start": 119.31,
        "duration": 0.78
    },
    {
        "text": "It's the candela,\nwhich has to do",
        "start": 120.09,
        "duration": 1.66
    },
    {
        "text": "with the light from a candle.",
        "start": 121.75,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": "LLOYD: Amp, is it?",
        "start": 123.33,
        "duration": 0.864
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: Amp, yeah.",
        "start": 124.194,
        "duration": 1.266
    },
    {
        "text": "[DING]",
        "start": 125.46,
        "duration": 1.04
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: OK,\nexplain amps-- yeah.",
        "start": 126.5,
        "duration": 1.75
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: It turns\nout the amp is a base",
        "start": 128.25,
        "duration": 1.35
    },
    {
        "text": "unit for historical reasons.",
        "start": 129.6,
        "duration": 1.59
    },
    {
        "text": "It was historically easier\nto measure the force",
        "start": 131.19,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "on wires with current than to\nmeasure individual charges.",
        "start": 133.17,
        "duration": 2.988
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: And then--\nbut coulombs are not--",
        "start": 136.158,
        "duration": 2.124
    },
    {
        "text": "huh.",
        "start": 138.282,
        "duration": 1.047
    },
    {
        "text": "We should write a letter.",
        "start": 139.329,
        "duration": 1.041
    },
    {
        "text": "[BOTH LAUGHING]",
        "start": 140.37,
        "duration": 1.327
    },
    {
        "text": " You should write\na comic about this.",
        "start": 141.697,
        "duration": 1.583
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah, yeah.",
        "start": 143.28,
        "duration": 1.16
    },
    {
        "text": " OK so there are--\nyeah, there are two more.",
        "start": 144.44,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "LLOYD: Mole.",
        "start": 146.45,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "[DING]",
        "start": 146.95,
        "duration": 0.47
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: It's\nrelated to temperature.",
        "start": 147.42,
        "duration": 1.65
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH:\nThere's kelvin.",
        "start": 149.07,
        "duration": 0.76
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: Yeah.",
        "start": 149.83,
        "duration": 0.37
    },
    {
        "text": "And there's kelvin, too.",
        "start": 150.2,
        "duration": 0.61
    },
    {
        "text": "[DING]",
        "start": 150.81,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": "That was just the warmup\nto let you know how mean",
        "start": 151.49,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "I would be with these riddles.",
        "start": 153.73,
        "duration": 1.31
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah.",
        "start": 155.04,
        "duration": 0.63
    },
    {
        "text": " So the actual riddle--\nthe real riddle.",
        "start": 155.67,
        "duration": 2.251
    },
    {
        "text": " Yes?",
        "start": 157.921,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": " There is a group of prisoners.",
        "start": 158.42,
        "duration": 2.292
    },
    {
        "text": "Do you want to pick a number?",
        "start": 160.712,
        "duration": 1.208
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: 100.",
        "start": 161.92,
        "duration": 0.425
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: 100 prisoners.",
        "start": 162.345,
        "duration": 0.915
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: Yeah.",
        "start": 163.26,
        "duration": 0.22
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: A city\nwith a lot of crime.",
        "start": 163.48,
        "duration": 1.749
    },
    {
        "text": "The evil warden decides she\nwants to play a sadistic game.",
        "start": 165.229,
        "duration": 3.551
    },
    {
        "text": "And so she tells all of the\nprisoners the night before,",
        "start": 168.78,
        "duration": 2.91
    },
    {
        "text": "the next day she's going to line\nthem up and put hats on them,",
        "start": 171.69,
        "duration": 2.94
    },
    {
        "text": "one of two colors.",
        "start": 174.63,
        "duration": 1.019
    },
    {
        "text": "Do you want to pick the colors?",
        "start": 175.649,
        "duration": 1.291
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: Ooh.",
        "start": 176.94,
        "duration": 0.54
    },
    {
        "text": "Purple and green.",
        "start": 177.48,
        "duration": 0.78
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: Purple and green.",
        "start": 178.26,
        "duration": 1.333
    },
    {
        "text": "You've got purple and green\nhats randomly on the prisoners.",
        "start": 179.593,
        "duration": 3.227
    },
    {
        "text": "It's going to be a random\nnumber of purple or green hats.",
        "start": 182.82,
        "duration": 2.49
    },
    {
        "text": "You don't have necessarily\n50 purple and 50 green.",
        "start": 185.31,
        "duration": 2.561
    },
    {
        "text": "What she says to the\nprisoners she's going to do",
        "start": 187.871,
        "duration": 1.999
    },
    {
        "text": "is line them up all\nfacing the same direction.",
        "start": 189.87,
        "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
        "text": "For example, the prisoner in\nthe back is looking forward",
        "start": 192.12,
        "duration": 2.67
    },
    {
        "text": "and can see all of the\nprisoners in front of him.",
        "start": 194.79,
        "duration": 2.576
    },
    {
        "text": "And then the next\nprisoner can see just",
        "start": 197.366,
        "duration": 1.624
    },
    {
        "text": "all the ones in front of him.",
        "start": 198.99,
        "duration": 1.208
    },
    {
        "text": "The prisoner at the front\ncan only see the wall.",
        "start": 200.198,
        "duration": 2.452
    },
    {
        "text": " Got it.",
        "start": 202.65,
        "duration": 1.65
    },
    {
        "text": " So then she's going\nto go from the back",
        "start": 204.3,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "and ask the prisoner\nthe color of her hat.",
        "start": 206.64,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "If she guesses correctly,\nshe gets to live.",
        "start": 209.34,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "If she guesses incorrectly,\nshe dies a silent death.",
        "start": 211.74,
        "duration": 3.566
    },
    {
        "text": "And then she goes to\nthe next prisoner.",
        "start": 215.306,
        "duration": 1.624
    },
    {
        "text": "Imagine that I'm behind you.",
        "start": 216.93,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": " OK.",
        "start": 218.18,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " And you're facing that way.",
        "start": 218.68,
        "duration": 0.91
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah.",
        "start": 219.59,
        "duration": 0.28
    },
    {
        "text": " And the warden comes\nto me and is like,",
        "start": 219.87,
        "duration": 1.53
    },
    {
        "text": "what color is your hat?",
        "start": 221.4,
        "duration": 0.958
    },
    {
        "text": "And I'm going to make my\nguess, or my educated guess,",
        "start": 222.358,
        "duration": 2.962
    },
    {
        "text": "and be like, green.",
        "start": 225.32,
        "duration": 1.42
    },
    {
        "text": "That's all you hear.",
        "start": 226.74,
        "duration": 1.29
    },
    {
        "text": "And then I will\neither die or not.",
        "start": 228.03,
        "duration": 1.65
    },
    {
        "text": "But you won't know.",
        "start": 229.68,
        "duration": 0.83
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah.",
        "start": 230.51,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " And then she'll come to you,\nand you'll make your guess.",
        "start": 231.01,
        "duration": 2.416
    },
    {
        "text": "Is there a strategy that\nprisoners can come up with",
        "start": 233.426,
        "duration": 2.134
    },
    {
        "text": "to maximize the\nnumber of prisoners",
        "start": 235.56,
        "duration": 2.82
    },
    {
        "text": "that are going to live?",
        "start": 238.38,
        "duration": 1.47
    },
    {
        "text": "So they can meet before,\nlike the night before.",
        "start": 239.85,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: But they can't\nlike look at each other's hat",
        "start": 242.13,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "and say.",
        "start": 243.63,
        "duration": 0.49
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: No.",
        "start": 244.12,
        "duration": 0.75
    },
    {
        "text": "She lines them up, then puts\nthe hats on of different colors.",
        "start": 244.87,
        "duration": 2.652
    },
    {
        "text": "They can't see their own hat.",
        "start": 247.522,
        "duration": 1.208
    },
    {
        "text": "They can only see the hats in\nthe prisoners in front of them.",
        "start": 248.73,
        "duration": 2.74
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH:\nDo they get to pick",
        "start": 251.47,
        "duration": 0.76
    },
    {
        "text": "how they line up in any way?",
        "start": 252.23,
        "duration": 0.78
    },
    {
        "text": "They're just randomly--",
        "start": 253.01,
        "duration": 0.87
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: Just randomly,\nand then randomly given hats.",
        "start": 253.88,
        "duration": 2.399
    },
    {
        "text": " And can they-- they can't\ninteract after they're lined",
        "start": 256.279,
        "duration": 2.166
    },
    {
        "text": "up?",
        "start": 258.445,
        "duration": 0.574
    },
    {
        "text": " The only thing\nthey can say is--",
        "start": 259.019,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "guess the color of their hats.",
        "start": 260.519,
        "duration": 1.687
    },
    {
        "text": " So they can talk\nto each other?",
        "start": 262.206,
        "duration": 1.374
    },
    {
        "text": " They can talk to each other\nto come up with a strategy",
        "start": 263.58,
        "duration": 2.352
    },
    {
        "text": "the night before.",
        "start": 265.932,
        "duration": 0.708
    },
    {
        "text": " But not the day of.",
        "start": 266.64,
        "duration": 0.874
    },
    {
        "text": "Uh.",
        "start": 267.514,
        "duration": 0.86
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm not--",
        "start": 268.374,
        "duration": 2.207
    },
    {
        "text": " It's a hard one.",
        "start": 270.581,
        "duration": 0.749
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah.",
        "start": 271.33,
        "duration": 1.1
    },
    {
        "text": " Try and maximize the\nnumber of survivors.",
        "start": 272.43,
        "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
        "text": " Right.",
        "start": 275.43,
        "duration": 0.624
    },
    {
        "text": " Not necessarily maximize--",
        "start": 276.054,
        "duration": 1.166
    },
    {
        "text": " Right.",
        "start": 277.22,
        "duration": 0.23
    },
    {
        "text": "Can you hear the person\nbehind you when they guess?",
        "start": 277.45,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": " Yes, you do.",
        "start": 279.05,
        "duration": 0.8
    },
    {
        "text": "[BOTH LAUGHING]",
        "start": 279.85,
        "duration": 1.836
    },
    {
        "text": " I mean, yeah, so the\nother thing you can do",
        "start": 281.686,
        "duration": 1.874
    },
    {
        "text": "is guess the same thing or\nguess the opposite thing,",
        "start": 283.56,
        "duration": 1.91
    },
    {
        "text": "but I don't see how that--",
        "start": 285.47,
        "duration": 0.82
    },
    {
        "text": " Well, the person behind\nyou can see your hat.",
        "start": 286.29,
        "duration": 1.958
    },
    {
        "text": " Oh, OK.",
        "start": 288.248,
        "duration": 0.794
    },
    {
        "text": "So you should always\nguess what the next person",
        "start": 289.042,
        "duration": 1.958
    },
    {
        "text": "is going to say.",
        "start": 291.0,
        "duration": 0.536
    },
    {
        "text": "So only one person dies, right?",
        "start": 291.536,
        "duration": 1.134
    },
    {
        "text": " Well, let's\nthink through that.",
        "start": 292.67,
        "duration": 1.375
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, so everyone can see all\nof the hats in front of them.",
        "start": 294.045,
        "duration": 2.745
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: Right, right.",
        "start": 296.79,
        "duration": 0.7
    },
    {
        "text": "So the next person\nwho's going to be up,",
        "start": 297.49,
        "duration": 1.46
    },
    {
        "text": "you should just say\nwhatever their hat is.",
        "start": 298.95,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: And then how many\ndoes that guarantee will live?",
        "start": 300.66,
        "duration": 2.37
    },
    {
        "text": "Like the strategy you're\nsaying, right, it's like you--",
        "start": 303.03,
        "duration": 2.291
    },
    {
        "text": "you say the--",
        "start": 305.321,
        "duration": 0.952
    },
    {
        "text": "the hat of the person\nin front of you?",
        "start": 306.273,
        "duration": 1.607
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah.",
        "start": 307.88,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " Say it's like green, purple,\ngreen, purple, green, purple.",
        "start": 308.38,
        "duration": 2.54
    },
    {
        "text": "Then everybody dies if you just\nsay the hat in front of you.",
        "start": 310.92,
        "duration": 2.99
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: Oh,\nbecause-- right, of course,",
        "start": 313.91,
        "duration": 1.15
    },
    {
        "text": "because they could die because\nthey gotta say the right thing.",
        "start": 315.06,
        "duration": 1.59
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: Exactly.",
        "start": 316.65,
        "duration": 0.27
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: I see.",
        "start": 316.92,
        "duration": 0.75
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah, you're right.",
        "start": 317.67,
        "duration": 0.9
    },
    {
        "text": "You're right-- yeah.",
        "start": 318.57,
        "duration": 0.44
    },
    {
        "text": " If it's lined up green,\npurple, green, purple,",
        "start": 319.01,
        "duration": 1.999
    },
    {
        "text": "and like every other person\nsays the hat in front of them,",
        "start": 321.009,
        "duration": 2.511
    },
    {
        "text": "the worst loss for\nthat one would be 50%.",
        "start": 323.52,
        "duration": 2.999
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah, but you could say\nit in a different pitch",
        "start": 326.519,
        "duration": 2.041
    },
    {
        "text": "to tell the next person\nwhether you're lying or not.",
        "start": 328.56,
        "duration": 2.166
    },
    {
        "text": "That should be your strategy.",
        "start": 330.726,
        "duration": 1.464
    },
    {
        "text": "Wasn't banned by the\nrules, I think, right?",
        "start": 332.19,
        "duration": 1.08
    },
    {
        "text": " It was not banned\nby the rules.",
        "start": 333.27,
        "duration": 1.395
    },
    {
        "text": "If every other person says\nthe hat in front of them,",
        "start": 334.665,
        "duration": 2.275
    },
    {
        "text": "then you guarantee 50%.",
        "start": 336.94,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": " Right.",
        "start": 338.19,
        "duration": 0.685
    },
    {
        "text": "Other than the cheat.",
        "start": 338.875,
        "duration": 0.875
    },
    {
        "text": " Was that-- was\nthat your guess?",
        "start": 339.75,
        "duration": 0.83
    },
    {
        "text": "LLOYD: Yeah.",
        "start": 340.58,
        "duration": 0.812
    },
    {
        "text": " Is there a way to\nget better than that?",
        "start": 341.392,
        "duration": 1.708
    },
    {
        "text": " Not counting my\ncheating method?",
        "start": 343.1,
        "duration": 1.75
    },
    {
        "text": "So the first person\ncould say something",
        "start": 344.85,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "about the total\ngroup with one word.",
        "start": 346.77,
        "duration": 2.42
    },
    {
        "text": "But like-- so you\ncould-- the first person",
        "start": 349.19,
        "duration": 1.75
    },
    {
        "text": "could say what the majority is.",
        "start": 350.94,
        "duration": 1.36
    },
    {
        "text": "Is that--",
        "start": 352.3,
        "duration": 0.69
    },
    {
        "text": " Or something like that?",
        "start": 352.99,
        "duration": 1.16
    },
    {
        "text": " Or something like that.",
        "start": 354.15,
        "duration": 1.415
    },
    {
        "text": " Ooh!",
        "start": 355.565,
        "duration": 0.695
    },
    {
        "text": " Shoot.",
        "start": 356.26,
        "duration": 0.96
    },
    {
        "text": " I went through this\nstruggle silently in my room.",
        "start": 357.22,
        "duration": 2.45
    },
    {
        "text": "And I made you do it on camera.",
        "start": 359.67,
        "duration": 1.34
    },
    {
        "text": " On camera.",
        "start": 361.01,
        "duration": 0.909
    },
    {
        "text": " This is a hint for you.",
        "start": 361.919,
        "duration": 1.041
    },
    {
        "text": "You have to figure\nout this thing",
        "start": 362.96,
        "duration": 1.315
    },
    {
        "text": "that you could look\nforward, see a whole group,",
        "start": 364.275,
        "duration": 1.958
    },
    {
        "text": "then decide something binary.",
        "start": 366.233,
        "duration": 1.687
    },
    {
        "text": " Right.",
        "start": 367.92,
        "duration": 1.07
    },
    {
        "text": " Like either it's this\nor it's that of the group.",
        "start": 368.99,
        "duration": 3.34
    },
    {
        "text": "So I've tortured you--",
        "start": 372.33,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": " Yes.",
        "start": 374.37,
        "duration": 0.83
    },
    {
        "text": " --with a physics trivia\nquestion and a really hard",
        "start": 375.2,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "riddle.",
        "start": 377.54,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " Yes.",
        "start": 378.04,
        "duration": 0.68
    },
    {
        "text": " Do you want to\nask me your riddle,",
        "start": 378.72,
        "duration": 1.594
    },
    {
        "text": "so I'm suffering while you--",
        "start": 380.314,
        "duration": 1.166
    },
    {
        "text": " That's a great idea.",
        "start": 381.48,
        "duration": 0.55
    },
    {
        "text": "OK.",
        "start": 382.03,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": "OK.",
        "start": 382.529,
        "duration": 0.603
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah, OK, so this is-- this\nis a Ray Smullyan riddle.",
        "start": 383.132,
        "duration": 3.542
    },
    {
        "text": "This is something I guess\nhe did at a lecture.",
        "start": 386.674,
        "duration": 1.916
    },
    {
        "text": "He-- it was at a math lecture,\nand he called some poor guy up.",
        "start": 388.59,
        "duration": 2.877
    },
    {
        "text": "And he said, I want to\nmake a deal with you.",
        "start": 391.467,
        "duration": 1.833
    },
    {
        "text": "And the deal is, I'm going\nto give you two $10 bills,",
        "start": 393.3,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "and then I'm going to make a\nstatement of some kind, just",
        "start": 395.52,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "any kind of logical statement.",
        "start": 397.23,
        "duration": 1.13
    },
    {
        "text": "And if the statement\nis false, you",
        "start": 398.36,
        "duration": 1.416
    },
    {
        "text": "give me back one\nof the $10 bills.",
        "start": 399.776,
        "duration": 1.564
    },
    {
        "text": "And if the statement\nis true, you keep both.",
        "start": 401.34,
        "duration": 1.38
    },
    {
        "text": "So would you agree to this?",
        "start": 402.72,
        "duration": 0.87
    },
    {
        "text": "It's a good deal, right?",
        "start": 403.59,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "You either get $10 or $20.",
        "start": 404.59,
        "duration": 1.421
    },
    {
        "text": "And so the guy says yes.",
        "start": 406.011,
        "duration": 0.999
    },
    {
        "text": "And then he says, OK-- and this\nis-- this is not the statement.",
        "start": 407.01,
        "duration": 2.63
    },
    {
        "text": "But he says, I'm going\nto say something,",
        "start": 409.64,
        "duration": 1.73
    },
    {
        "text": "and then you're going\nto owe me $1,000.",
        "start": 411.37,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "And the question\nis, what can he say",
        "start": 413.07,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "that will result in\nhim being owed $1,000.",
        "start": 414.57,
        "duration": 3.11
    },
    {
        "text": "Raymond Smullyan\nwould get $1,000.",
        "start": 417.68,
        "duration": 1.9
    },
    {
        "text": "It's just a statement.",
        "start": 419.58,
        "duration": 1.212
    },
    {
        "text": "The other guy doesn't interact\nanymore at this point.",
        "start": 420.792,
        "duration": 2.208
    },
    {
        "text": " But does-- does the\nother have $1,000?",
        "start": 423.0,
        "duration": 1.75
    },
    {
        "text": "Those",
        "start": 424.75,
        "duration": 0.55
    },
    {
        "text": " Well, that's his problem.",
        "start": 425.3,
        "duration": 0.88
    },
    {
        "text": "He's gotta cough it up.",
        "start": 426.18,
        "duration": 0.958
    },
    {
        "text": "[BOTH LAUGHING]",
        "start": 427.138,
        "duration": 0.676
    },
    {
        "text": " OK, so he may go into debt.",
        "start": 427.814,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": " Now you're suffering, too.",
        "start": 431.174,
        "duration": 1.166
    },
    {
        "text": "[BOTH LAUGHING]",
        "start": 432.34,
        "duration": 2.35
    },
    {
        "text": "[MUSIC PLAYING]",
        "start": 434.69,
        "duration": 2.83
    },
    {
        "text": " Is it something like, in\norder for you to figure out",
        "start": 437.52,
        "duration": 2.73
    },
    {
        "text": "whether this statement is\ntrue, you need to give me $900?",
        "start": 440.25,
        "duration": 4.65
    },
    {
        "text": " In the sense that that's\nlike a logic statement,",
        "start": 444.9,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "it's that sort of structure, but\nit's not even that complicated.",
        "start": 447.48,
        "duration": 3.755
    },
    {
        "text": " It's not even\nthat complicated.",
        "start": 451.235,
        "duration": 1.375
    },
    {
        "text": " No, no.",
        "start": 452.61,
        "duration": 1.444
    },
    {
        "text": " I feel like I'm\ngetting nowhere.",
        "start": 454.054,
        "duration": 1.416
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah, yeah.",
        "start": 455.47,
        "duration": 1.19
    },
    {
        "text": " Is it something like\na qualifier, where--",
        "start": 456.66,
        "duration": 3.03
    },
    {
        "text": "is it something like,\neither you will keep $10",
        "start": 459.69,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "and give me back $1,010,\nor you will keep $20",
        "start": 462.81,
        "duration": 4.26
    },
    {
        "text": "and give me back $1,020?",
        "start": 467.07,
        "duration": 1.06
    },
    {
        "text": "Money",
        "start": 468.13,
        "duration": 0.8
    },
    {
        "text": " No, because then you\ncould just not do it,",
        "start": 468.93,
        "duration": 1.24
    },
    {
        "text": "and the statement\nwould be false,",
        "start": 470.17,
        "duration": 0.98
    },
    {
        "text": "and you'd only have\nto give back $10.",
        "start": 471.15,
        "duration": 1.541
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah, I've though that\nthat might be a-- a fly",
        "start": 472.691,
        "duration": 2.652
    },
    {
        "text": "in my ointment.",
        "start": 475.343,
        "duration": 0.627
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah.",
        "start": 475.97,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "[LAUGHING] Yeah, yeah.",
        "start": 476.47,
        "duration": 0.59
    },
    {
        "text": "There's-- there's a condition\nwhere you can escape.",
        "start": 477.06,
        "duration": 1.65
    },
    {
        "text": " Ugh!",
        "start": 478.71,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "[BOTH LAUGHING]",
        "start": 479.21,
        "duration": 2.85
    },
    {
        "text": "I think-- I think that I'm done.",
        "start": 482.06,
        "duration": 1.334
    },
    {
        "text": " All right, let's--",
        "start": 483.394,
        "duration": 0.832
    },
    {
        "text": " In the time--",
        "start": 484.226,
        "duration": 0.794
    },
    {
        "text": "in the time allotted--",
        "start": 485.02,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": " [LAUGHING]",
        "start": 486.46,
        "duration": 1.01
    },
    {
        "text": " I'm ready.",
        "start": 487.47,
        "duration": 0.51
    },
    {
        "text": " For the answer?",
        "start": 487.98,
        "duration": 0.55
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah.",
        "start": 488.53,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " The answer is he will\nsay, you will either",
        "start": 489.03,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": "give me $1,000 or $10.",
        "start": 491.07,
        "duration": 1.059
    },
    {
        "text": "You have to think for a second\nabout why this is true, right?",
        "start": 492.129,
        "duration": 2.541
    },
    {
        "text": "So--",
        "start": 494.67,
        "duration": 0.33
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: Yeah.",
        "start": 495.0,
        "duration": 0.912
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: So if he--",
        "start": 495.912,
        "duration": 1.189
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: Oh!",
        "start": 497.101,
        "duration": 0.749
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: Right?",
        "start": 497.85,
        "duration": 0.78
    },
    {
        "text": "So, yeah, he can't give him the\n$10, because then the statement",
        "start": 498.63,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "is false.",
        "start": 500.64,
        "duration": 0.58
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: OK.",
        "start": 501.22,
        "duration": 1.35
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH:\n[LAUGHING] Yeah.",
        "start": 502.57,
        "duration": 0.77
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: I get it.",
        "start": 503.34,
        "duration": 0.75
    },
    {
        "text": "That's what I was\ntrying to get, was",
        "start": 504.09,
        "duration": 1.29
    },
    {
        "text": "like there's something in\nthe statement that guarantees",
        "start": 505.38,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "that it's either true or false.",
        "start": 507.57,
        "duration": 1.22
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: Right.",
        "start": 508.79,
        "duration": 0.44
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: And\nthat's the \"you",
        "start": 509.23,
        "duration": 1.416
    },
    {
        "text": "will give me $10,\" is what\ncontradicts the statement.",
        "start": 510.646,
        "duration": 2.574
    },
    {
        "text": "ZACH WEINERSMITH: Right.",
        "start": 513.22,
        "duration": 0.26
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANNA COWERN: Because if\nit's $10, then it's false.",
        "start": 513.48,
        "duration": 2.179
    },
    {
        "text": "But then he is doing\nwhat the thing is.",
        "start": 515.659,
        "duration": 2.303
    },
    {
        "text": " Right.",
        "start": 517.962,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " So it can't be false.",
        "start": 518.462,
        "duration": 0.764
    },
    {
        "text": "It has to be true.",
        "start": 519.226,
        "duration": 0.714
    },
    {
        "text": " Yes.",
        "start": 519.94,
        "duration": 0.395
    },
    {
        "text": " Ugh!",
        "start": 520.335,
        "duration": 0.395
    },
    {
        "text": " That was a great riddle.",
        "start": 520.73,
        "duration": 0.79
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah, I like that one.",
        "start": 521.52,
        "duration": 0.57
    },
    {
        "text": " OK, are you ready?",
        "start": 522.09,
        "duration": 0.9
    },
    {
        "text": " Yes.",
        "start": 522.99,
        "duration": 0.569
    },
    {
        "text": " So the solution\nthat guarantees",
        "start": 523.559,
        "duration": 2.101
    },
    {
        "text": "the most survivors does have\nto do with odds and evens.",
        "start": 525.66,
        "duration": 2.49
    },
    {
        "text": " OK.",
        "start": 528.15,
        "duration": 0.66
    },
    {
        "text": " If the person in\nthe back says purple,",
        "start": 528.81,
        "duration": 2.43
    },
    {
        "text": "that means there's an odd\nnumber of purple hats ahead.",
        "start": 531.24,
        "duration": 2.724
    },
    {
        "text": " OK.",
        "start": 533.964,
        "duration": 0.968
    },
    {
        "text": " And-- and then the next\nperson will know what they are.",
        "start": 534.932,
        "duration": 4.528
    },
    {
        "text": "So the person in the back will\nsay either green or purple",
        "start": 539.46,
        "duration": 4.59
    },
    {
        "text": "and determine the total--",
        "start": 544.05,
        "duration": 1.74
    },
    {
        "text": "like, of the rest of\nthe hats, is there",
        "start": 545.79,
        "duration": 2.49
    },
    {
        "text": "an odd number of purple hats or\nan even number of purple hats?",
        "start": 548.28,
        "duration": 2.996
    },
    {
        "text": " OK.",
        "start": 551.276,
        "duration": 0.614
    },
    {
        "text": " And they're telling\neverybody that.",
        "start": 551.89,
        "duration": 2.07
    },
    {
        "text": "So then the next person can\nsee the rest of the hats",
        "start": 553.96,
        "duration": 4.25
    },
    {
        "text": "and sees, OK, well--",
        "start": 558.21,
        "duration": 2.55
    },
    {
        "text": " Dammit!",
        "start": 560.76,
        "duration": 1.29
    },
    {
        "text": " That's it.",
        "start": 562.05,
        "duration": 0.6
    },
    {
        "text": "That's beautiful.",
        "start": 562.65,
        "duration": 1.438
    },
    {
        "text": " You guys both, at the\nsame time, you're like, oh!",
        "start": 564.088,
        "duration": 4.302
    },
    {
        "text": " Oh, that's great.",
        "start": 568.39,
        "duration": 1.484
    },
    {
        "text": " Isn't it nice?",
        "start": 569.874,
        "duration": 0.666
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah, that's really good.",
        "start": 570.54,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": "[LAUGHING]",
        "start": 571.79,
        "duration": 1.66
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah, so if you look down the\nline and you know it's odd,",
        "start": 573.45,
        "duration": 4.115
    },
    {
        "text": "and there's an equal number\nof other kinds of hats,",
        "start": 577.565,
        "duration": 2.125
    },
    {
        "text": "you know you must be the odd\nman out-- the odd person out.",
        "start": 579.69,
        "duration": 2.46
    },
    {
        "text": " Yes.",
        "start": 582.15,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": " And if it's not,\nthen you know you must",
        "start": 583.73,
        "duration": 1.724
    },
    {
        "text": "align with the missing spot.",
        "start": 585.454,
        "duration": 1.166
    },
    {
        "text": " Yes.",
        "start": 586.62,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " And so now you have\nan answer to your--",
        "start": 587.12,
        "duration": 2.67
    },
    {
        "text": " [LAUGHING AND CLAPPING]",
        "start": 589.79,
        "duration": 1.173
    },
    {
        "text": " That's-- that's really--\nthat's really irritating.",
        "start": 590.963,
        "duration": 2.227
    },
    {
        "text": "You and I both like got\nright up to that last step.",
        "start": 593.19,
        "duration": 2.35
    },
    {
        "text": " Yes.",
        "start": 595.54,
        "duration": 0.88
    },
    {
        "text": "You got so close.",
        "start": 596.42,
        "duration": 1.12
    },
    {
        "text": "Thank you so much.",
        "start": 597.54,
        "duration": 0.751
    },
    {
        "text": " Thank you for having me.",
        "start": 598.291,
        "duration": 1.082
    },
    {
        "text": " This is-- this is\nsuch a coincidence.",
        "start": 599.373,
        "duration": 1.657
    },
    {
        "text": "I happened to be in London\nand going to BAHFest.",
        "start": 601.03,
        "duration": 3.03
    },
    {
        "text": " BAHFest.",
        "start": 604.06,
        "duration": 0.74
    },
    {
        "text": " Just one last thing.",
        "start": 604.8,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": " (BOTH) Happy physics-ing.",
        "start": 606.88,
        "duration": 1.712
    },
    {
        "text": " That was the best\nfirst try ever.",
        "start": 608.592,
        "duration": 1.458
    },
    {
        "text": " I nailed it.",
        "start": 610.05,
        "duration": 0.376
    },
    {
        "text": "I was so good at that.",
        "start": 610.426,
        "duration": 0.754
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah.",
        "start": 611.18,
        "duration": 0.41
    },
    {
        "text": "Bam.",
        "start": 611.59,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " Yes.",
        "start": 612.09,
        "duration": 0.58
    },
    {
        "text": "Hey, one last thing.",
        "start": 612.67,
        "duration": 0.851
    },
    {
        "text": "It's that time of year again--",
        "start": 613.521,
        "duration": 1.249
    },
    {
        "text": "Christmas!",
        "start": 614.77,
        "duration": 0.72
    },
    {
        "text": "Just kidding.",
        "start": 615.49,
        "duration": 0.63
    },
    {
        "text": "PBS Digital Studios\nis running a survey.",
        "start": 616.12,
        "duration": 1.839
    },
    {
        "text": "And basically, they'd\nlike to hear from you",
        "start": 617.959,
        "duration": 1.791
    },
    {
        "text": "what you'd like to see more of\non YouTube and in the world.",
        "start": 619.75,
        "duration": 3.03
    },
    {
        "text": "So, it's a quick survey.",
        "start": 622.78,
        "duration": 1.037
    },
    {
        "text": "There's a link to the\ndescription and in the card.",
        "start": 623.817,
        "duration": 2.083
    },
    {
        "text": "And 25 random participants are\ngoing to get a PBS T-shirt,",
        "start": 625.9,
        "duration": 2.67
    },
    {
        "text": "so sounds worth it.",
        "start": 628.57,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "That's all.",
        "start": 630.01,
        "duration": 0.66
    },
    {
        "text": "Thanks.",
        "start": 630.67,
        "duration": 1.55
    }
